Business Brief -- Kerr-McGee Corp.:
   Oklahoma Company to Cut
   Capital Expenditures 31%
About 60% of the 1992 budget, or $220 million, will be
spent on oil and gas projects, down about 33% from last year.
Most will be spent in the Gulf of Mexico and onshore U.S. and
Canada. The rest of the oil and gas budget, or 45%, will go
to projects in the North Sea.
   The Oklahoma City energy, chemicals and coal concern said
it will fund development of the company's coal reserves in
Illinois and Wyoming at twice last year's level of $20
million.